genresAdvancedInfo.name: haitian dance
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Haitian dance music is a vibrant and rhythmic genre that draws from various styles such as kompa, rara, and zouk. It features lively percussion, horns, and call-and-response vocals. Haitian dance music is often associated with celebrations and cultural events, and its infectious beats have gained popularity around the world. The genre has also influenced other styles such as salsa and merengue.
